gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 108, Kings 107
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns outscored the Kings, 30-22 in the fourth and ended the game on a 12-4 run in the final four minutes to win, 108-107. Kevin Durant (28 points, five rebounds) and Devin Booker (21 points, four rebounds, six assists) led Phoenix as Bradley Beal added 20 points, nine rebounds, and four assists. Domantas Sabonis led the Kings with 25 points, 12 rebounds, and nine assists while DeAaron Fox (23 points, five rebounds, six assists, four steals.
